@startuml Specification_LonelyStudent_v20

Use Case ID: UC1
Brief description: UC1 allows an unregistered user to create an account
Primary actor: Unregistered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: The user is not logged in and has access to the registration page
Main Flow of Events:
1. The unregistered user navigates to the registration page.
2. The user fills out the registration form with required information (e.g., email, password, full name).
3. The user submits the registration form.
4. The system creates a new account.
Alternative Flows: Email is already in use
Post-conditions: User account is created

Use Case ID: UC2
Brief description: UC2 allows an unregistered user to view public content (read-only)
Primary actor: Unregistered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is not logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. The unregistered user navigates to the application.
2. User can view public notes, public files, public study plans.
3. User can read comments on public content.
4. All content is read-only (no editing).
Alternative Flows: No public content available
Post-conditions: Public content is displayed to the user

Use Case ID: UC3
Brief description: UC3 allows a registered user to log in to their account
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: The user has a valid account and is not logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Log in" option.
2. User enters their email and password.
3. System verifies the credentials.
4. If credentials are valid, the user is logged in and redirected to the dashboard.
Alternative Flows: Invalid credentials, Account locked
Post-conditions: User is logged in

Use Case ID: UC4
Brief description: UC4 allows a registered user to manage their profile
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Manage Profile" option.
2. User can edit personal information (name, email, faculty, birth date, study year, study type).
3. User can upload or change profile avatar.
4. User submits the updated profile information.
5. System updates the user's profile in the database.
Alternative Flows: Invalid input data, Avatar upload failed
Post-conditions: User's profile is updated in the system

Use Case ID: UC5
Brief description: UC5 allows a registered user to create a tag (formerly subject)
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Create Tag" option.
2. User fills out the tag creation form (tag name, description, visibility).
3. User submits the tag creation form.
4. System creates a new tag and associates it with the user.
Alternative Flows: Missing required information, Tag name already exists
Post-conditions: Tag is created and added to the user's tag list

Use Case ID: UC6
Brief description: UC6 allows a registered user to edit or delete a tag
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing tag
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects an existing tag to edit or delete.
2. If editing, user modifies the tag details and submits the updated information.
3. If deleting, user confirms the deletion of the tag.
4. System updates or deletes the tag in the database based on the user's action.
Alternative Flows: Invalid input data, Deletion confirmation denied
Post-conditions: Tag is updated or deleted in the system

Use Case ID: UC7
Brief description: UC7 allows a registered user to create a task
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Create Task" option.
2. User fills out the task creation form (task name, description, tag, study plan, due date, priority).
3. User submits the task creation form.
4. System creates a new task and adds it to the user's task list.
Alternative Flows: Missing required information
Post-conditions: Task is created and added to the user's task list

Use Case ID: UC8
Brief description: UC8 allows a registered user to edit or delete a task
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing task
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects the task they want to edit or delete.
2. If editing, user modifies the task details and submits the updated information.
3. If deleting, user confirms the deletion of the task.
4. System updates or deletes the task in the database based on the user's action.
Alternative Flows: Invalid input data, Deletion confirmation denied
Post-conditions: Task is updated or deleted in the system

Use Case ID: UC9
Brief description: UC9 allows a registered user to mark a task as complete or favorite
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing task
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects the task they want to update.
2. User chooses to mark the task as complete or toggle favorite status.
3. System updates the task state in the database.
Alternative Flows: Invalid state selection
Post-conditions: Task state is updated in the system

Use Case ID: UC10
Brief description: UC10 allows a registered user to filter tasks
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has existing tasks
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects the filter option.
2. User chooses the filter criteria (by tag, by due date, by status, by priority).
3. System displays the filtered list of tasks based on the selected criteria.
Alternative Flows: Invalid filter criteria, No tasks match the filter
Post-conditions: Filtered list of tasks is displayed to the user

Use Case ID: UC11
Brief description: UC11 allows a registered user to create a note
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Create Note" option.
2. User fills out the note creation form (note title, note content, visibility).
3. User submits the note creation form.
4. System creates a private note for the user.
Alternative Flows: Missing required information
Post-conditions: Note is created and added to the user's note list

Use Case ID: UC12
Brief description: UC12 allows a registered user to edit or delete a note
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing note
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects the note they want to edit or delete.
2. If editing, user modifies the note details and submits the updated information.
3. If deleting, user confirms the deletion of the note.
4. System updates or deletes the note in the database based on the user's action.
Alternative Flows: Invalid input data, Deletion confirmation denied
Post-conditions: Note is updated or deleted in the system

Use Case ID: UC13
Brief description: UC13 allows a registered user to select text in a note and add a comment
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing note
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects text in the note they want to comment on.
2. User clicks "Add Comment" option.
3. User fills out the comment creation form (comment text, visibility).
4. User submits the comment creation form.
5. System creates a new comment linked to the selected text range.
Alternative Flows: Missing required information, Invalid text selection
Post-conditions: Comment is created and linked to the note text

Use Case ID: UC14
Brief description: UC14 allows a registered user to edit or delete a comment on a note
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing comment on a note
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects the comment they want to edit or delete.
2. If editing, user modifies the comment text and submits the updated information.
3. If deleting, user confirms the deletion of the comment.
4. System updates or deletes the comment in the database based on the user's action.
Alternative Flows: Invalid input data, Deletion confirmation denied
Post-conditions: Comment is updated or deleted in the system

Use Case ID: UC15
Brief description: UC15 allows a registered user to request publication of a note
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: Administrator
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing private note
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects a private note they want to publish.
2. User clicks "Request Publication" option.
3. System marks the note as "pending approval".
4. System notifies administrators of the publication request.
Alternative Flows: Note is already public, Note is already pending approval
Post-conditions: Publication request is created and awaits admin approval

Use Case ID: UC16
Brief description: UC16 allows an administrator to approve or reject publication requests
Primary actor: Administrator
Secondary actors: System, Registered user
Preconditions: Administrator is logged in and has pending publication requests
Main Flow of Events:
1. Administrator views the list of pending publication requests.
2. Administrator selects a request and reviews the content.
3. Administrator clicks "Approve" or "Reject".
4. If approved, system marks the content as public and notifies the user.
5. If rejected, system keeps the content private and notifies the user with reason.
Alternative Flows: Content violates policies, No pending requests
Post-conditions: Publication request is processed and user is notified

Use Case ID: UC17
Brief description: UC17 allows a registered user to create a study plan
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Create Study Plan" option.
2. User fills out the study plan creation form (name, description, faculty, start date, end date, visibility).
3. User submits the study plan creation form.
4. System creates a new study plan and adds it to the user's plan list.
Alternative Flows: Missing required information
Post-conditions: Study plan is created and added to the user's study plan list

Use Case ID: UC18
Brief description: UC18 allows a registered user to edit, delete, or publish a study plan
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: Administrator
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing study plan
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects the study plan they want to edit, delete, or publish.
2. If editing, user modifies the study plan details and submits the updated information.
3. If deleting, user confirms the deletion of the study plan.
4. If publishing, user submits a publication request that goes to administrators.
5. System updates, deletes, or marks the study plan for approval based on the user's action.
Alternative Flows: Invalid input data, Deletion confirmation denied
Post-conditions: Study plan is updated, deleted, or marked for admin approval

Use Case ID: UC19
Brief description: UC19 allows a registered user to create a lesson
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Create Lesson" option.
2. User fills out the lesson creation form (title, content, tag, study plan, order).
3. User submits the lesson creation form.
4. System creates a new lesson and associates it with the user's tag or study plan.
Alternative Flows: Missing required information
Post-conditions: Lesson is created and added to the system

Use Case ID: UC20
Brief description: UC20 allows a registered user to edit or delete a lesson
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing lesson
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects the lesson they want to edit or delete.
2. If editing, user modifies the lesson details and submits the updated information.
3. If deleting, user confirms the deletion of the lesson.
4. System updates or deletes the lesson in the database based on the user's action.
Alternative Flows: Invalid input data, Deletion confirmation denied
Post-conditions: Lesson is updated or deleted in the system

Use Case ID: UC21
Brief description: UC21 allows a registered user to upload files associated with a lesson
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has an existing lesson
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects a lesson and clicks "Upload File".
2. User selects a file from their device.
3. System uploads the file to cloud storage (S3, blob storage) and generates a unique storage key (GUID).
4. System creates a FILE_RECORD in the database with reference to the lesson.
5. System displays the uploaded file in the lesson.
Alternative Flows: File upload failed, File size exceeds limit, Invalid file type
Post-conditions: File is uploaded and associated with the lesson

Use Case ID: UC22
Brief description: UC22 allows a registered user to delete files from a lesson
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has files in a lesson
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects a lesson with files.
2. User clicks "Delete File" next to the file they want to remove.
3. User confirms the deletion.
4. System deletes the file from storage and removes the FILE_RECORD from the database.
Alternative Flows: Deletion confirmation denied, File not found
Post-conditions: File is deleted from the lesson and storage

Use Case ID: UC23
Brief description: UC23 allows a registered user to manage calendar events
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects "Create Calendar Event" option.
2. User fills out the event creation form (event name, date, time, location, tag).
3. User submits the event creation form.
4. System creates a new event and adds it to the user's calendar.
5. User can also edit or delete existing calendar events.
Alternative Flows: Missing required information, Invalid input data
Post-conditions: Calendar event is created, updated, or deleted in the system

Use Case ID: UC24
Brief description: UC24 allows a registered user to share entities (study plans, lessons, notes) with other users
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System, Other registered users
Preconditions: User is logged in and has entities to share
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects an entity (study plan, lesson, note) they want to share.
2. User clicks "Share" option and selects users or groups to share with.
3. User sets permissions (VIEW, EDIT, ADMIN).
4. System creates SHARE records in the database.
5. System notifies the shared users of the new shared content.
Alternative Flows: User not found, Sharing permission denied
Post-conditions: Entity is shared with specified users and permissions are set

Use Case ID: UC25
Brief description: UC25 allows a registered user to revoke sharing of entities
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: User is logged in and has shared entities
Main Flow of Events:
1. User selects a shared entity and clicks "Manage Sharing".
2. User selects the user they want to revoke access from.
3. User confirms the revocation.
4. System removes the SHARE record from the database.
5. System notifies the affected user that access has been revoked.
Alternative Flows: Revocation confirmation denied
Post-conditions: Entity is no longer shared with the specified user

Use Case ID: UC26
Brief description: UC26 allows an administrator to moderate and remove inappropriate content
Primary actor: Administrator
Secondary actors: System
Preconditions: Administrator is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. Administrator selects "Content Moderation" option.
2. Administrator can review user avatars, shared files, public notes, and comments.
3. If inappropriate content is found, administrator can flag or remove it.
4. System removes the inappropriate content and notifies the user.
5. System may log the action for audit purposes.
Alternative Flows: No inappropriate content found, Content already removed
Post-conditions: Inappropriate content is removed from the system

Use Case ID: UC27
Brief description: UC27 allows a registered user to view their own public content and find other public content
Primary actor: Registered user
Secondary actors: Other registered users, System
Preconditions: User is logged in
Main Flow of Events:
1. User can view public notes, lessons, and study plans shared by other users.
2. User can search or filter by tag, author, or keywords.
3. User can read comments and discussions on public content.
4. All interactions with public content are read-only (except own content).
Alternative Flows: No public content available, Search returns no results
Post-conditions: Public content is displayed to the user

@enduml